OL,3,CAll you need to know about local
OL,4,Celections in Yorkshire and Lincolnshire
OL,6,FThe new combined authority will
OL,7,Freceive #540million of government
OL,8,Ffunding over the next 30 years, and
OL,9,Fthe mayor will have the power to spend
OL,10,Fthat money on key local priorities
OL,11,Fsuch as transport, education and
OL,12,Fhousing.
OL,14,FThey will also oversee the police and
OL,15,Ffire services - taking over duties
OL,16,Fcurrently held by the police, fire and
OL,17,Fcrime commissioner.
OL,19,FVoters in West Yorkshire will elect a
OL,20,Fmayor for a second time.
